<task id="011" project="spaarke-datagrid-framework-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>SavedQueryService + 2 endpoints: GET savedquery/{id} (1h cache) + GET savedqueries/{entity} (1h cache)</title>
    <phase>2: Phase B — BFF Passthrough</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>010</dependencies>
    <blocks>015,016,017</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, api, auth, cache, dataverse</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>2 BFF endpoints + service + cache + auth filter; ADR-008 + ADR-019 + ADR-028 + ADR-029 + bff-extensions.md binding</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>B1</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Author `SavedQueryService` (cached projection) + 2 BFF endpoints in `Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Dataverse/`: `GET /api/dataverse/savedquery/{savedQueryId}` returning `{ entityName, fetchXml, layoutXml, name }` and `GET /api/dataverse/savedqueries/{entityLogicalName}` returning `[{ id, name, isDefault, queryType }]`. Both use `IDistributedCache` with 1-hour TTL. Both apply `DataverseAuthorizationFilter` per ADR-008.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in ASP.NET Core Minimal APIs, `IDistributedCache` (Redis in prod), `ServiceClient` Dataverse SDK, ADR-008 endpoint filter pattern. Familiar with `Sprk.Bff.Api` DI/configuration.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Two new endpoints live in `Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Dataverse/DataverseEndpoints.cs` (or `SavedQueryEndpoints.cs`), each backed by `SavedQueryService` with 1-hour cache, ADR-008 filter applied, ProblemDetails on errors. `dotnet build` passes; `dotnet test` for the new service passes; cache hit ratio >95% verifiable post-deploy.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-BFF-01 + FR-BFF-02. `RetrieveSavedQuery` via `ServiceClient.Retrieve("savedquery", id, ColumnSet)`; `RetrieveSavedQueriesForEntity` via `RetrieveMultiple` with FetchXML filter `statecode=0 AND returnedtypecode={entityCode} AND querytype=0`. Cache key shape: `dv:savedquery:{id}` and `dv:savedqueries:{entityLogicalName}`. Service uses app-only auth (managed identity) on the Dataverse side; user JWT is for authorization filter only.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Dataverse/DataverseEndpoints.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Dataverse/SavedQueryService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Dataverse/DataverseAuthorizationFilter.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Dataverse/Models/SavedQueryDto.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Dataverse/SavedQueryServiceTests.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">`DataverseAuthorizationFilter` applied to both endpoints — 403 ProblemDetails on Read-privilege deny.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Errors return ProblemDetails (RFC 7807) — not raw exceptions.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Authentication via JWT on incoming request; service-side uses managed identity for `ServiceClient`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">No new NuGet packages without size baseline check; verify `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` reveals no new HIGH CVEs.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Placement Justification (from task 010) referenced in PR description; endpoints mapped unconditionally (no feature flag); corresponding tests in task 016 acknowledged.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Cache TTL exactly 1 hour per FR-BFF-01/02 (`TimeSpan.FromHours(1)`).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">`SavedQueryService` is `internal` class with explicit `IDistributedCache` injection — NOT `IMemoryCache`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Per `bff-extensions.md` test obligation: unit tests for cache hit/miss + happy path + 403 filter behavior MUST be added in task 016 (not skipped).</constraint>
  </constraints>

