  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Given a valid savedQueryId, when `GET /api/dataverse/savedquery/{id}` is called twice within 1 hour, then the second call returns from cache (verify via telemetry / log).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given a request without proper Read privilege on the target entity, when endpoint called, then 403 ProblemDetails is returned (not 200 with empty data).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`, when run, then zero errors.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive`, when run, then no new HIGH CVEs.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given publish size measurement, when compared to baseline, then within ADR-029 budget.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Parallels tasks 012, 013, 014 (Wave B1 — all depend on task 010 and touch separate service files). The 1-hour cache TTL is intentional for dev friction (savedquery edits won't appear instantly) — accepted in R1 per spec.
  </notes>

